ok. You know what?

304
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:21,080
Maybe she should focus on the ghost that's
haunting her right now,don't you think?

305
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:23,340
Yeah,ok-yes.
I do.

306
00:15:23,450 --> 00:15:24,330
What's my job again?

307
00:15:24,380 --> 00:15:25,950
Check the plane manifest.

308
00:15:25,990 --> 00:15:27,120
Ok.

309
00:15:28,850 --> 00:15:31,550
You and I have a field trip to go on.

310
00:15:40,490 --> 00:15:42,700
come on,Let's go find daniel.

311
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:43,570
Why?

312
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:46,720
Because this is probably
near where he died.

313
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:48,730
It will help him remember what happened.

314
00:15:48,810 --> 00:15:50,470
But why look for him at all?

315
00:15:50,490 --> 00:15:52,360
I mean,he hasn't bugged me
in hours. Maybe he's finished.

316
00:15:52,390 --> 00:15:54,660
No,he's not finished
until he crosses over-

317
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:56,200
until we help him cross over.

318
00:15:56,230 --> 00:15:58,160
How many times did I tell you?

319
00:15:58,190 --> 00:15:59,910
I don't like being left behind!

320
00:15:59,950 --> 00:16:01,590
Becca,talk to him.

321
00:16:01,650 --> 00:16:02,500
Find out what he needs.

322
00:16:02,540 --> 00:16:03,910
Please,don't go.

323
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:05,110
Ask him what's keeping him here.

324
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:07,450
Why won't you just leave me alone?

325
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:08,740
They left me here.

326
00:16:08,770 --> 00:16:10,790
They never said a word!

327
00:16:10,820 --> 00:16:11,670
Were they punishing me?

328
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:13,320
What was I supposed to think?

329
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:15,810
Who? Daniel,who left you here?

330
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:17,020
Who is she,anyway?

331
00:16:17,060 --> 00:16:18,580
I don't like her.

332
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,510
Becca,find out what's keeping him here.

333
00:16:20,560 --> 00:16:21,980
I don't care.

334
00:16:22,790 --> 00:16:25,910
I hate him! I want him to go away!

335
00:16:34,460 --> 00:16:35,930
i'm burning

336
00:16:37,770 --> 00:16:39,420
Hey,what do you see?

337
00:16:39,670 --> 00:16:41,090
Daniel,talk to me,all right?

338
00:16:41,110 --> 00:16:42,880
I want to help you.
She wants to help you!

339
00:16:42,910 --> 00:16:44,790
She doesn't want to help me!

340
00:16:45,470 --> 00:16:46,510
Why should I help her?

341
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:47,810
Well,then,stop hurting her,all right?

342
00:16:47,830 --> 00:16:49,320
Let her go.

343
00:16:50,290 --> 00:16:51,490
Hey.

344
00:16:52,110 --> 00:16:53,080
What happened?

345
00:16:53,130 --> 00:16:54,900
I was on fire!

346
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:56,520
It was horrible.

347
00:16:57,230 --> 00:16:59,680
Look,I know how painful this is,ok?

348
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:01,270
But look at me.

349
00:17:01,350 --> 00:17:03,530
I'm right here. We're ok.

350
00:17:04,740 --> 00:17:07,600
There's a reason that he
told you all of that. Ok?

351
00:17:07,630 --> 00:17:09,290
He was trying to tell
you what happened to him,

352
00:17:09,330 --> 00:17:11,580
and with that,you can cross him over.

353
00:17:11,620 --> 00:17:12,420
I don't care.

354
00:17:12,460 --> 00:17:13,360
Yes,you do.

355
00:17:13,390 --> 00:17:15,200
You want to help him and yourself.

356
00:17:15,210 --> 00:17:17,660
I don't care about
daniel or any of them!

357
00:17:17,700 --> 00:17:19,240
You can't give up.

358
00:17:19,290 --> 00:17:21,040
Yes,I can!

359
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:22,220
I'm done.

360
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:24,330
I'm never going to do that again.

361
00:17:38,350 --> 00:17:40,180
Still not hungry?

362
00:17:45,670 --> 00:17:47,610
You know,your parents are
going to be here tomorrow,

363
00:17:47,650 --> 00:17:50,080
so we don't really have much time.

364
00:17:53,370 --> 00:17:56,410
Has a ghost ever done
anything like this to you?

365
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:01,250
I've seen weird things before.

366
00:18:01,270 --> 00:18:03,190
No one's ever tried to hurt me.

367
00:18:03,230 --> 00:18:05,580
I know how awful this is.

368
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:07,850
But the vision,it'S...

369
00:18:08,060 --> 00:18:10,680
sometimes the only way they can
tell you that they need your help.

370
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:14,320
But why should i help daniel when
all he tries to do is scare me?

371
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:21,190
Look... I know that this is not fair.

372
00:18:22,110 --> 00:18:25,930
Most kids don't have to think about
death until they're much older.

373
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,790
But you and me?

374
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,920
Our lives are different.

375
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:34,850
You want a reason why
you should help daniel?

376
00:18:35,330 --> 00:18:39,100
One is because if you
don't,he'll never leave you alone.

377
00:18:40,060 --> 00:18:42,920
But the real reason is because you can.

378
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:45,900
Ok.

379
00:18:46,490 --> 00:18:48,020
But how?

380
00:18:48,050 --> 00:18:49,710
The vision.

381
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:53,100
Tell me everything you saw.

382
00:19:05,740 --> 00:19:07,930
There were bodies on the ground.

383
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:09,940
I'm right here.

384
00:19:10,370 --> 00:19:11,990
I was on fire.

385
00:19:13,020 --> 00:19:14,890
You mean daniel was.

386
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:20,210
At first,his skin hurt really bad.

387
00:19:20,710 --> 00:19:23,080
Then,he couldn't feel anything.

388
00:19:27,940 --> 00:19:30,050
There was metal burning.

389
00:19:31,350 --> 00:19:33,210
And tires.

390
00:19:33,670 --> 00:19:35,690
And there were cars.

391
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:39,060
They looked like tinfoil
somebody punched really hard.

392
00:19:40,820 --> 00:19:43,050
One of them was on fire.

393
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:45,470
I think that one was daniel'S.

394
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:48,040
Can you see a license plate number?

395
00:19:48,870 --> 00:19:51,980
There were
letters. M-I-Y...

396
00:19:52,940 --> 00:19:54,880
the number 8.

397
00:20:01,320 --> 00:20:02,620
Hey...

398
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:05,140
becca.

399
00:20:05,690 --> 00:20:08,070
No. You did great.

400
00:20:09,330 --> 00:20:11,780
You know what? Let's get out of here.

401
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:12,960
What do you think?

402
00:20:12,990 --> 00:20:14,050
Let's go...

403
00:20:14,090 --> 00:20:16,160
walk amongst the living
for a little while.

404
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:18,010
Can I just be alone?

405
00:20:19,780 --> 00:20:21,200
Sure.

406
00:20:22,170 --> 00:20:23,930
Hey,melinda?

407
00:20:27,740 --> 00:20:30,040
Were you ever scared?

408
00:20:31,820 --> 00:20:33,840
It's never been easy.

409
00:20:34,930 --> 00:20:39,080
But I had someone
who... made me feel brave.

410
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:43,050
I hope I can do that same thing for you.

411
00:20:45,530 --> 00:20:46,490
Hey.

412
00:20:46,530 --> 00:20:48,290
How'd the open house
for the new listing go?

413
00:20:48,330 --> 00:20:51,640
Oh,people loved the cookies,but
not bites on the house.

414
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:53,350
I brought leftovers.

415
00:20:53,360 --> 00:20:54,990
Thanks for covering.

416
00:20:55,590 --> 00:20:56,270
Where's becca?

417
00:20:56,320 --> 00:20:57,420
She's at home resting.

418
00:20:57,460 --> 00:20:58,550
Jim's there.

419
00:20:58,590 --> 00:20:59,550
How's she doing?

420
00:20:59,590 --> 00:21:00,920
We made some progress.

421
00:21:00,930 --> 00:21:03,090
I think I know who the
little boy in the woods is.

422
00:21:03,140 --> 00:21:04,880
He's looking for his parents.

423
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:07,180
2 cars hit
head-on,causing a pile-up.

424
00:21:07,210 --> 00:21:09,340
There were 5
fatalities,including a family¡ª

425
00:21:09,370 --> 00:21:11,700
becca had seen their
license plate in a vision¡ª

426
00:21:11,710 --> 00:21:14,900
a mother,father,and a 13-year-old
boy named daniel asher.

427
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:15,650
That's terrible.

428
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:16,730
Daniel died at the scene.

429
00:21:16,770 --> 00:21:18,610
And his parents died
later at the hospital.

430
00:21:18,660 --> 00:21:20,720
You know,maybe they just saw
the light and went right into it.

431
00:21:20,740 --> 00:21:22,730
And he's just been
waiting there ever since?

432
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:24,240
He thinks they're still alive?

433
00:21:24,290 --> 00:21:25,580
I'm not sure.

434
00:21:25,630 --> 00:21:29,270
But he needs to know that they've
gone,and he should join them.

435
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:31,580
With any luck,becca will be
able to convince him of that.

436
00:21:31,610 --> 00:21:32,630
It would really help them both.

437
00:21:32,660 --> 00:21:34,860
You know what? I really have to go.

438
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:41,910
Hey.

439
00:21:41,940 --> 00:21:42,970
You're back!

440
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,240
That's so great.

441
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:46,470
Um,you could come meet my parents.

442
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:48,870
So,I was telling them all
about how you helped me.

443
00:21:48,910 --> 00:21:51,220
Now,I admit that I was just
pretending to see ghosts,

444
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:53,580
just like you did when you
were my age for attention.

445
00:21:53,630 --> 00:21:56,820
Melinda. I'm joan cahill,becca's mom.

446
00:21:56,860 --> 00:21:58,250
I don't even know what to say.

447
00:21:58,290 --> 00:22:00,120
Honestly,I don't,either.

448
00:22:00,150 --> 00:22:03,050
Honey,the cahills were able
to get an earlier flight.

449
00:22:03,100 --> 00:22:04,500
Um,this is tony.

450
00:22:04,540 --> 00:22:05,820
Tony,this is my wife melinda.

451
00:22:05,870 --> 00:22:09,710
Thank you for saving our daughter-
our whole family,actually.

452
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:11,740
Well,I don't know if I really helped.

453
00:22:11,760 --> 00:22:13,060
You did.

454
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:15,830
Look,I don't know how
you got through to her,

455
00:22:15,870 --> 00:22:20,920
but these things that she was
imagining,we didn't know what to do.

456
00:22:20,950 --> 00:22:24,770
Frankly,I felt like we'd lost
her long before she ran away.

457
00:22:25,180 --> 00:22:29,230
But... you're back now. Right,sweetheart?

458
00:22:29,410 --> 00:22:31,170
Things are going to be a-ok.

459
00:22:32,930 --> 00:22:36,230
Yeah. A-ok,again.

460
00:22:44,940 --> 00:22:46,170
Thanks for not busting me.

461
00:22:46,220 --> 00:22:48,190
So,what are you going to do now?

462
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:51,470
Every time you see a
ghost,just ignore it?

463
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:53,110
Kind of already tried that.

464
00:22:53,150 --> 00:22:55,200
- Yeah,but it will be easier now.
- How?

465
00:22:55,220 --> 00:22:57,170
'Cause I know it's not my fault.

466
00:22:57,190 --> 00:22:58,860
Before,I thought I had
something bad in me.

467
00:22:58,900 --> 00:23:00,970
I was making them come
to me and nobody else.

468
00:23:00,990 --> 00:23:03,720
They come to you
because you can see them.

469
00:23:04,100 --> 00:23:06,740
And because they need your help.

470
00:23:07,010 --> 00:23:09,630
Look,this is who you really are.

471
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:13,760
It's who we both are.

472
00:23:14,290 --> 00:23:15,780
No.

473
00:23:16,780 --> 00:23:18,920
I'm not brave enough.

474
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:38,100
You comfortable,sweetie?

475
00:23:39,050 --> 00:23:41,590
You can't hear a word
I'm saying,can you?

476
00:23:50,270 --> 00:23:53,440
I could sleep for about
100 years,you know?

477
00:23:53,810 --> 00:23:55,400
Should we try to get a
later flight tomorrow?

478
00:23:55,450 --> 00:23:58,070
No. Let's get home.

479
00:23:59,580 --> 00:24:02,120
Thank god,we can throw these away now.

480
00:24:02,990 --> 00:24:06,170
What were we doing,making
her take these?

481
00:24:08,700 --> 00:24:09,990
Joan,wait...

482
00:24:10,990 --> 00:24:13,000
she wasn't hallucinating.

483
00:24:13,050 --> 00:24:15,110
She never actually saw anything.

484
00:24:15,150 --> 00:24:19,030
I know. I hope it's
over,but just in case...

485
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:30,960
it's not just about becca.

486
00:24:31,260 --> 00:24:35,310
It's about that little boy in the woods
waiting on parents that will never come back.

487
00:24:35,340 --> 00:24:37,070
Yeah,but becca knows
about the light now.

488
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:39,420
So maybe she's able to help him.

489
00:24:40,030 --> 00:24:41,470
And he knows about you.

490
00:24:41,510 --> 00:24:42,800
He can come to you.

491
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:45,700
And what about the ghost
that haunts her after that?

492
00:24:46,020 --> 00:24:47,410
And then,the one after that?

493
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:50,590
Honey,no one could have
helped her more than you did.

494
00:24:51,190 --> 00:24:52,730
Yeah.

495
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:56,540
That's what kills me.

496
00:25:23,220 --> 00:25:25,170
No. Get away from them.

497
00:25:33,120 --> 00:25:36,380
I'd give anything just to
be with my parents again.

498
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:48,040
Oh! No,no. Why can't
you just leave me alone?

499
00:25:48,070 --> 00:25:50,270
Because then I'd be alone,too.

500
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,900
How'd you like it if I left
you in the dark in those woods?

501
00:25:52,930 --> 00:25:54,060
I begged you to.

502
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:55,670
But you didn't mean it.

503
00:25:56,210 --> 00:25:57,760
Why can't you just be my friend?

504
00:25:57,810 --> 00:25:59,130
Because you're dead!

505
00:25:59,190 --> 00:26:02,490
You'd be dead,too,if I didn't
help you find food and water.

506
00:26:02,650 --> 00:26:03,810
I looked out for you.

507
00:26:03,850 --> 00:26:06,610
Every night,I was there,and you knew it.

508
00:26:06,650 --> 00:26:10,000
Ok. Fine. You watched over me. Thanks.

509
00:26:10,020 --> 00:26:11,420
Now,go,please.

510
00:26:11,460 --> 00:26:13,070
I'm still protecting you.

511
00:26:13,100 --> 00:26:14,010
What's that supposed to mean?

512
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:16,730
Someone knows about you
and your friend. That lady.

513
00:26:16,770 --> 00:26:19,400
- He found me,and he'll find you,too.
- Who?

514
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:20,510
I'm not sure.

515
00:26:20,550 --> 00:26:23,290
He wanted me to come
with him,but I wouldn'T.

516
00:26:23,510 --> 00:26:27,750
He said he knows where
they're keeping my parents.

517
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:29,340
I don't understand.

518
00:26:29,370 --> 00:26:30,930
Melinda knows things.
You should go to her.

519
00:26:30,980 --> 00:26:35,040
No. She just wants to send me away
so I'll never see my parents again.

520
00:26:36,260 --> 00:26:37,600
Becca...

521
00:26:38,670 --> 00:26:40,410
